WEBVTT

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:14.640
Hello, you're watching The One Show,
live on BBC One and iPlayer.

00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:17.879
With Alex Jones
and JB Gill.

00:00:17.879 --> 00:00:20.359
Now as it's Wednesday,
Matt's in for Watchdog.

00:00:20.359 --> 00:00:23.480
And if you're one of the millions
of people watching with a pension,

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.679
you'll want to listen up.

00:00:26.679 --> 00:00:28.839
Yes, I'll be telling
you about the pension provider

00:00:28.839 --> 00:00:31.559
that's left some customers locked
out of their life savings.

00:00:31.559 --> 00:00:34.640
Plus, our inbox was inundated
on Easter Monday with complaints

00:00:34.640 --> 00:00:37.280
about a cancelled P&O cruise that
let people know just 24

00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:40.640
hours before departure.

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:43.240
We'll be telling you how to claim
back costs if you're

00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:45.560
left out of pocket.

00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:47.840
Thanks, Matt, that's coming
up in just a moment.

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:50.560
Also tonight - we'll be joined
by Max Beesley and newcomer

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:53.079
Edison Alcaide who star
in a new thought provoking drama

00:00:53.079 --> 00:00:57.320
called Suspect: The Shooting
of Jean Charles de Menezes.

00:00:57.320 --> 00:01:00.439
Set 20 years ago, in the aftermath
of the 7/7 bombings,

00:01:00.439 --> 00:01:03.840
it focuses on the real life events
that led to an innocent young

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:06.439
man being fatally shot
on the London Underground

00:01:06.439 --> 00:01:09.280
after he was mistaken
for a terrorist.

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:12.439
Max and Edison will be telling us
what it was like to bring

00:01:12.439 --> 00:01:14.719
such a powerful story
to the small screen.

00:01:14.719 --> 00:01:18.000
And joining us later in the show
is Oscar nominated actor

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:21.079
Dame Imelda Staunton
and her daughter Bessie Carter -

00:01:21.079 --> 00:01:24.400
who'll you know from Bridgerton -
as they prepare to take to the stage

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:26.719
for the first time playing
