Martin was never defined by his
language and learning difficulties,

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:49.719
he was never held back by downs
syndrome, he would say,

00:01:49.719 --> 00:01:51.640
you and me, I'm happy.

00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:57.120
What that means is
being in the moment.

00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:59.519
Such a heart-warming film,
you won't want to miss that!

00:01:59.519 --> 00:02:02.719
But first, it's Matt for Watchdog
with that story about pensions.

00:02:02.719 --> 00:02:05.840
Yes, it's meant to be your ticket
to retirement, the pot of gold

00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:08.080
at the end of your working rainbow.

00:02:08.080 --> 00:02:10.879
So finding out you can't access it?

00:02:10.879 --> 00:02:17.520
Well, it's not just frustrating,
it can put your plans on pause.

00:02:17.520 --> 00:02:19.879
Imagine that there's
cash in your account,

00:02:19.879 --> 00:02:24.000
but you can't access it
through no fault of your own.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.599
Well, that's what some customers
of one of the country's largest

00:02:27.599 --> 00:02:29.039
pension providers have been
experiencing over

00:02:29.039 --> 00:02:32.199
the last few months.

00:02:32.199 --> 00:02:35.639
Aegon boasts around 4 million
customers across the UK.

00:02:35.639 --> 00:02:37.759
One of them is Beyata,
a self-employed cake

00:02:37.759 --> 00:02:41.159
maker from Brighton.

00:02:41.159 --> 00:02:48.919
I started a pension 20 years ago,
so I didn't pay too much attention.

00:02:48.919 --> 00:02:51.759
Now I'm becoming 57 and I would
like to exit my money.

00:02:51.759 --> 00:02:54.879
Wanting to use the money to buy
a property, Beyata tried to log

00:02:54.879 --> 00:02:57.560
into her Aegon account to check how
much she had saved.

00:02:57.560 --> 00:03:00.800
But she hit a brick wall.

00:03:00.800 --> 00:03:03.599
I want to know how much
I've got in the pot.

00:03:03.599 --> 00:03:08.400
You would like to see how
you want to exit, the tax you pay.

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:10.560
So when you go in, what do you find?

00:03:10.560 --> 00:03:11.759
Well, nothing at the moment.

00:03:11.759 --> 00:03:15.479
The website isn't working.

00:03:15.479 --> 00:03:17.159
Confused, Beyata called up
Aegon customer services

00:03:17.159 --> 00:03:19.120
who told her the website was down.

00:03:19.120 --> 00:03:22.240
Instead, she was sent an online form
and was assured she would get

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:23.639
a response within five working days.

00:03:23.639 --> 00:03:25.439
But she didn't hear anything.

00:03:25.439 --> 00:03:27.560
There is no phone call,
there is no letter.

00:03:27.560 --> 00:03:28.599
There's nothing.

00:03:28.599 --> 00:03:35.439
Instead, took Aegon 18 days
to send Beyata a letter,

00:03:35.439 --> 00:03:38.080
telling her she had over £22,000
in her pension savings pot

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:39.520
and explaining how to withdraw it.

00:03:39.520 --> 00:03:41.400
But despite repeated attempts,
she still couldn't get

00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:43.159
access to her money.

00:03:43.159 --> 00:03:46.960
What is the communication
with Aegon at the moment?

00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:49.439
There is no communication,
only the letter we've received.

00:03:49.439 --> 00:03:51.080
I'm waiting.

00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:59.039
What does this mean for you,
Beyata, and your family?

00:03:59.319 --> 00:04:01.240
It affects me hugely
because obviously you find

00:04:01.240 --> 00:04:03.840
a property, but I can't exchange
so I'm waiting for it.

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:05.039
So it's very, very frustrating.

00:04:05.039 --> 00:04:07.199
Beyata's case is just
the tip of the iceberg.

00:04:07.199 --> 00:04:09.400
There are loads of complaints online
from disgruntled customers.

00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:12.240
Since the start of the year,
58% of Aegon reviews on Trustpilot

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:20.199
have ranked just one star.

00:04:22.279 --> 00:04:24.680
The customers we've heard
from haven't been given a timeframe

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:27.079
for when they will be able
to access their money.

00:04:27.079 --> 00:04:29.759
And in our research we also heard
that it is affecting

00:04:29.759 --> 00:04:31.920
people who don't even hold
an account with them.

00:04:31.920 --> 00:04:33.600
Eight months ago, self-employed
tradesman Gary decided

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:36.000
to leave Aegon having been
with the providers since 2010.

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.560
However, he discovered three
contributions of £778 had been

00:04:38.560 --> 00:04:44.519
taken from him by Aegon
after closing his account.

00:04:44.519 --> 00:04:47.519
So Gary complained to the company.

00:04:47.519 --> 00:04:50.160
Then they came back and said
we shouldn't have taken it.

00:04:50.160 --> 00:04:53.399
It can take a little while to sort
out, possibly 28 days.

00:04:53.399 --> 00:04:58.120
But 28 days later, there
was still no sign of the £2300.

00:04:58.120 --> 00:05:05.560
When you explained what was
happening, what did they say?

00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:09.360
When I rang up I said could be
a week or could it be six months?

00:05:09.360 --> 00:05:10.560
Sorry, there is no timescale.

00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:13.199
But despite making regular calls
to Aegon there was still no

00:05:13.199 --> 00:05:14.240
sign of Gary's cash.

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:15.680
Just continually ringing
their customer service.

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:22.639
Very frustrating.

00:05:22.639 --> 00:05:25.519
And I just feel you're banging your
head against a brick wall.

00:05:25.519 --> 00:05:28.639
Two years ago a new set of rules
was introduced known as consumer

00:05:28.639 --> 00:05:31.040
duty which requires FCA regulated
firms to prove they deliver

00:05:31.040 --> 00:05:32.079
good customer outcomes.

00:05:32.079 --> 00:05:34.240
If they don't, they can
be hit with penalties.

00:05:34.240 --> 00:05:37.240
James Daly is from the financial
research group Fairer Finance.

00:05:37.240 --> 00:05:39.879
It doesn't sound like Aegon has done
enough at this point.

00:05:39.879 --> 00:05:42.079
Customers seem
incredibly frustrated.

00:05:42.079 --> 00:05:47.319
They've been made promises
which Aegon didn't keep.

00:05:47.319 --> 00:05:50.439
If they were seen to be stalling
and not doing what was best

00:05:50.439 --> 00:05:52.120
for their customers,
then penalties would be

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:54.000
even greater for them.

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:57.600
To say we are going to have this
sorted in a few days and then

00:05:57.600 --> 00:05:59.759
continually let customers down,
just adds insult to injury.

00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:01.199
We asked Aegon for a comment.

00:06:01.199 --> 00:06:02.839
It sincerely apologised
for any frustration

00:06:02.839 --> 00:06:08.079
and inconvenience caused.

00:06:08.079 --> 00:06:10.959
It said that a technology upgrade
left a small number of customers

00:06:10.959 --> 00:06:13.360
experiencing issues which may have
led to delays in service.

00:06:13.360 --> 00:06:17.120
But that no one would be financially
disadvantaged as a result.

00:06:17.120 --> 00:06:20.079
Aegon assured us that its customers'
money is safe and secure

00:06:20.079 --> 00:06:22.240
and that its executive team
is working to improve

00:06:22.240 --> 00:06:29.480
customer experience.

00:06:29.480 --> 00:06:32.120
After we got in touch,
Aegon did reimburse Gary his £2300

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:34.519
and Beyata successfully cashed
out her pension pot, with both

00:06:34.519 --> 00:06:37.720
receiving gestures of goodwill.

00:06:37.720 --> 00:06:40.040
Aegon, you've been trusted to look
after people's money.

00:06:40.040 --> 00:06:42.399
So don't let them down when,
after years, they need

00:06:42.399 --> 00:06:48.800
to access their funds.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.040
You really feel for them.

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:53.720
t's so frustrating when you've got
money that you just can't access.

00:06:53.720 --> 00:06:55.600
Absolutely, Al.

00:06:55.600 --> 00:06:58.480
And if you feel you've been treated
unfairly by a pension provider,

00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:00.759
or any company for that matter,
get in touch.

00:07:00.759 --> 00:07:05.040
watchdog@bbc.co.uk,
@BBCWatchdog on the socials.

00:07:05.040 --> 00:07:08.439
Another company that's back
in our inbox is Klarna,

00:07:08.439 --> 00:07:11.720
the buy now pay later service.

00:07:11.720 --> 00:07:13.639
Last year, we told you how
fraudulent accounts

00:07:13.639 --> 00:07:16.160
were being set
up in people's names.

00:07:16.160 --> 00:07:18.639
At the time, Klarna told us it had

00:07:18.639 --> 00:07:23.240
industry-leading fraud prevention
methods in place to protect users.

00:07:23.240 --> 00:07:25.160
I'm guessing that those
measures haven't held up?

00:07:25.160 --> 00:07:27.399
You got it, JB.

00:07:27.399 --> 00:07:30.279
We've heard from a number of people
who say fraudulent Klarna accounts

00:07:30.279 --> 00:07:33.399
have been set up in their name
and now they're left with hundreds

00:07:33.399 --> 00:07:34.600
of pounds worth of debt.

00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:36.439
Take Craig.

00:07:36.439 --> 00:07:38.920
Al, hit it.

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:41.759
Craig received a letter from Klarna
issuing a final demand

00:07:41.759 --> 00:07:44.680
for a payment of £495,
but he hadn't used

00:07:44.680 --> 00:07:48.800
Klarna since 2023.

00:07:48.800 --> 00:07:51.680
Once he checked his credit score
and discovered it was affected,

00:07:51.680 --> 00:07:54.079
he contacted Klarna who confirmed
someone had indeed set up

00:07:54.079 --> 00:07:57.560
an account in his name.

00:07:57.560 --> 00:08:02.639
Sadly Craig isn't alone.

00:08:02.639 --> 00:08:03.959
JB, tell us about Carl.

00:08:03.959 --> 00:08:06.360
He discovered he had
a Klarna account in his name

00:08:06.360 --> 00:08:08.759
with a debt of over £600,
even though he's never

00:08:08.759 --> 00:08:09.800
been a customer.

00:08:09.800 --> 00:08:12.680
He told Klarna it couldn't possibly
have been him making the purchases

00:08:12.680 --> 00:08:15.319
as he was with his family in Canada
at the time.

00:08:15.319 --> 00:08:17.959
Yes, and he's since had calls
from a debt collection agency,

00:08:17.959 --> 00:08:20.439
which has taken a big toll on him.

00:08:20.439 --> 00:08:22.680
It's really frustrating
and incredibly stressful.

00:08:22.680 --> 00:08:25.279
I'm looking to buy a house
later in the year.

00:08:25.279 --> 00:08:27.680
And the idea of something
like this putting a spanner

00:08:27.680 --> 00:08:30.399
in the works is unbearable.

00:08:30.399 --> 00:08:32.120
That must be so stressful.

00:08:32.120 --> 00:08:35.080
What has Klarna said about this?

00:08:35.080 --> 00:08:38.559
Klarna says the fraudsters
would have already had compromised

00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:41.399
data to open these accounts,
but it is really sorry for how

00:08:41.399 --> 00:08:46.840
these cases were handled.

00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:49.240
It says a stronger verification
process has now been introduced

00:08:49.240 --> 00:08:52.360
meaning customers will have to take
a live selfie along with a photo

00:08:52.360 --> 00:08:54.039
of their ID if fraud is suspected.

00:08:54.039 --> 00:08:55.799
And what about Craig and Carl?

00:08:55.799 --> 00:08:58.679
Klarna recognises that it didn't act
quick enough to resolve the issues

00:08:58.679 --> 00:09:01.799
and since we got involved they both
have now had their debts removed

00:09:01.799 --> 00:09:05.720
along with any marks
on their credit reports.

00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:13.679
What a result for Watchdog!

00:09:14.399 --> 00:09:16.080
Thank you, studio!

00:09:16.080 --> 00:09:18.480
Hopefully Klarna will clear up
any other similar cases just

00:09:18.480 --> 00:09:20.399
as quickly without needing
a nudge from us.

00:09:20.399 --> 00:09:21.840
Let us know if they don't.

00:09:21.840 --> 00:09:28.600
