00:10:40.799 --> 00:10:45.759
situation?

00:10:46.120 --> 00:10:47.559
Hold the cruise company to account.

00:10:47.559 --> 00:10:49.240
It's the one that took your money.

00:10:49.240 --> 00:10:52.120
If the ship's not available then
it's got to sort you out.

00:10:52.120 --> 00:10:54.759
Only then should you go
to your insurer, because of course,

00:10:54.759 --> 00:10:56.919
if you have to claim,
you could see your

00:10:56.919 --> 00:10:58.120
premiums go up next time.

00:10:58.120 --> 00:11:00.759
Which made us worry about tomorrow,
when The Aurora is off

00:11:00.759 --> 00:11:01.960
to Norway for 12 nights.

00:11:01.960 --> 00:11:05.120
P&O say she's ship-shape
and Bristol fashion,

00:11:05.120 --> 00:11:08.559
pining for the fjords.

00:11:08.559 --> 00:11:11.200
If you're Oslo-bound on the Aurora,
still no harm in checking

00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:15.000
before leaving the house.

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:18.600
Send us a postcard of
the Northern Lights!

00:11:18.600 --> 00:11:20.240
Thanks, Matt.

00:11:20.240 --> 00:11:23.679
Lots of great advice as always.

